> Crispy pan-fried gnocchi with crème fraîche is super tasty and incredibly easy to make! The gnocchi has a crispy coating and a pillow-like centre, accompanied by 'meaty' chestnut mushrooms, tasty broccoli, cheese and flat leaf parsley. This twist on a classic Italian dish makes our own delicacy!

Peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{3}(roughly chopped). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{2}(finely chopped). Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil for later.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add your mushrooms in small batches and cook until they go golden brown, then remove from the pan. Add the chopped echalion shallot and garlic to the now empty pan and reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} until softened, if the pan gets too dry add a splash of water.

Return your mushrooms to the pan along with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}, the @water{100%ml} and a few good grinds of @ground black pepper{}. Allow to simmer over medium heat for ~{8-10%minutes} until thickened.

In another frying pan, heat a splash of @oil{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @gnocchi{300%g}. Gently fry for ~{8%minutes} until it's crispy around the edges. Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{250%g} up into small florets. Plunge into the pot of boiling water for ~{3%minutes}, then remove, drain and keep to the side.

Stir the @crème fraîche{1} into your mushroom sauce. Once heated through, add your gnocchi and your broccoli to the sauce and give it all a good stir. Taste for seasoning and add more salt and pepper as you wish.

Divide your gnocchi between your bowls and top with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{2} and your chopped parsley.